DIRGE
The Flagon's Sentry — Maven's Quiet Answer
AP 16 (Master-tier band, 15-25) — player-legal build, itemized below
"Lanterns." / "Dirge."

Wiry Breton, crossbow across his knees, the barrel at the Ratway fork (Ch.20). The
Guild's outer security: he decides who passes, prices what they want, and forgets
nothing. When Maven finally assembles what she already holds on the Grelod kill
(factions/the black-briars, IV-V), Dirge is the hand she sends — probably AFTER
Ivarstead, on the road to Bleak Falls (scratch §11, LOCKED).

THE SCENE (locked): he finds them and shares a calm, friendly MEAL first — easy,
warm, the road-tradition nod. Then: "Welp. Best get to it." — and he starts trying
to kill them. His heart is not in it. If he starts LOSING, he tries to de-escalate.
If he KILLS ONE of them, he stops immediately — "Well, job's done." — nods —
"Lanterns." — and leaves. Bittersweet and a little funny: a friend doing a job he
doesn't relish. The contract is the contract.

