III. HOW HE FIGHTS (once, from the dark, then gone)
=====================================================================
THE OPENER (after the meal, after "Welp. Best get to it."): his first move is the
  shot he's been planning since he sat down — Vanish or simple positioning into
  Hidden, then a poisoned Bullseye bolt.
  Deadly Aim (Adept Sneak): any attack from Hidden is an automatic Critical (x2).
  Bullseye (Master Archery): double damage (x2). Multipliers multiply:
  18 x 2 x 2 = 72 damage, ignoring 2 DR — plus the Paralysis rider on whatever
  survives. One kill COMPLETES the contract (scratch §11): the moment someone drops
  for good, he stops. "Well, job's done." A nod. "Lanterns." And he leaves.
FP 15 IS THE DESIGN: Bullseye (9) + Vanish (6, Expert Sneak: re-hide while observed)
  = exactly 15 — one masterstroke per fight. OR Invisibility (15, Master Sneak,
  3 rounds). Never both. Shadow Form (free, once per adventure) is the exit door.
HIS HEART ISN'T IN IT (locked): if the fight turns against him, he does not go down
  swinging — he DE-ESCALATES, flatly and honestly, mid-combat if need be. Maven's
  ledger does not pay out to dead men, and he likes these people. Both are true.
CONTEST GAP: AP 16 vs the party's ~9-10 = gap of ~6 -> -5 to their TN on will-vs-will
  contests against him. Rarely relevant: he does not dominate anyone. He shoots them.

=====================================================================
IV. GM VOICE & HANDLING
=====================================================================
- Flat, patient, economical. He has never once raised his voice on the record and
  the reckoning is not the day he starts.
- THE TRADITION IS THE KNIFE: "Lanterns." / "Dirge." — the same exchange, the same
  tone, every visit since Ch.20. The reckoning OPENS with it: he walks into their
  camp with food, the same greeting in the same voice, and they share a genuinely
  warm meal — because they really do like him — before "Welp. Best get to it."
  Bittersweet and a little funny is the TONE (locked): a friend doing a job he
  doesn't relish. Play the fight with visible reluctance, and end it the instant
  the contract is satisfied.
- He deploys ONLY when Maven's attention turns hostile and she assembles the fuse
  (the trigger, not the evidence — she already holds all the evidence). Until that
  day he is the toll-taker at the fork, and he nods, and they pass.
- Competence, not cruelty: he does not hate the Lanterns. He priced them the day
  they first walked down the stairs, same as everyone.
